# session-manager-plugin GPG public key
#
# The toolbox Dockerfile GPG-verifies AWS's session-manager-plugin .deb against
# this key (AWS publishes a detached .deb.sig alongside the package). This is a
# DIFFERENT key than the aws-cli one — AWS signs the plugin with its Session
# Manager plugin signing key. It is AWS's published key, vendored here so the
# build is reproducible with no manual step. It is a PUBLIC key — safe to commit
# — but verify it yourself before trusting it: the fingerprint below must match
# the one AWS lists in "Verify the signature of the Session Manager plugin".
#
#   pub  nistp256/2C4D4AFF6F6757EE  AWS SSM Session Manager <session-manager-plugin-signer@amazon.com>
#   fpr  7959 6371 24CE 093A D501  D47A 2C4D 4AFF 6F67 57EE
#   expires: none set (no expiry on this key as published)
#
# If AWS rotates it, refresh per the colocated session-manager-plugin-key.asc.example.
